   The year 2009 was the 150th anniversary of the publication of "On the
   Origin of Species by Means of Natural Selection" and the 200th
   anniversary of Darwin's birth.
   This web site was created to celebrate these events and provide the
   general public, students and teachers with entertaining explorations of
   life’s origin and evolution.
   A general audience will find here an entertaining exploration (videos
   and animations) and teachers a rich source of documents (films,
   simulations and teaching materials) to plan innovative and exciting
   lessons.
   All documents are free, and the associated licence (see terms of use)
   simplifies their use for educational purposes.

   You will find a description of the web site on the "user guide" page .
   For questions or feedback please use the contact form.
   Visit our page on facebook   and on youtube

MEDEA Awards

   Evolution of life is the winner for European collaboration at the MEDEA
   Awards 2010, a competition recognising and rewarding excellence and
   creativity in media in education.
